City of Portland sends delinquent tax notices to …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 05:08 PM PDT

housands of Portlanders are being told they owe delinquent taxes. However, some claim they already paid, shaking their confidence in the city.

7,463 people have letters saying they never paid the metro’s supportive housing services tax and 4,514 notices went out for non-payment of the county’s Preschool For All program.

This only impacts people in a higher tax bracket, specifically if you have an annual income over $125,000 or you’re filing jointly and making more than $200,000 a year.

Oregon whooping cough cases increase 770%, prompting …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:48 PM PDT

As of May 29, 178 pertussis cases have been reported to OHA in 2024, compared to 20 cases reported at that time in 2023. The warnings about pertussis — also known as whooping cough — come amid an increasing number of Oregon children falling behind on immunizations, according to the Oregon Health Authority.

Washington sees increase in out-of-state abortion …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:47 PM PDT

After the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade in 2022, Washington state has seen an increase in out-of-state patients seeking an abortion than before the high court struck down the case, according to a University of Washington study.

Researchers found a 50% increase in out-of-state patients — largely from Texas and Alaska– compared to 4-6% before the Supreme Court’s Dobbs v. Jackson Women’s Health decision, which overturned Roe v. Wade.

Swim warning issued after high E. coli levels found …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:43 PM PDT

Visitors to Battle Ground Lake are being cautioned against taking a swim after high levels of E. coli were found in water samples collected from the lake by Clark County Public Health on Tuesday.

Dog attacks on postal workers rise

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:41 PM PDT

Portland is number 20 on the top 25 list for cities nationwide with the most dog bite incidents against mail carriers. Nationwide, more than 5,800 postal employees were attacked by dogs last year. 19 of those happened in Portland.

American Red Cross blood supply ‘critically’ low: …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:27 PM PDT

The American Red Cross is calling for blood donors as incoming blood supplies are “critically” low due to a recent lack of donors, the nonprofit organization announced Thursday. In the past month, the Red Cross collected 20,000 fewer blood donations than is needed to maintain its national blood supply.

Two Portland State University students allege unlawful …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:26 PM PDT

Two Portland State University students intend to file a lawsuit against the school alleging unlawful use of force by officers during an on-campus protest against violence in Gaza, according to tort claim notices obtained by KOIN 6 News.

Providence and nurses union gear up for contract …

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:24 PM PDT

Nurses from six Providence hospitals are gearing up to be part of contract negotiations set to start next week for the Oregon Nurses Association union.

OHSU, Legacy sign ‘definitive’ merger agreement

Video / May 30, 2024 / 04:19 PM PDT

In what is being called the largest healthcare merger in Oregon history, OHSU offered to take the financially struggling Legacy Health System under its wing, with the two organizations signing a letter of intent to combine their care back in August 2023. Legacy’s clinics and hospitals would now become part of OHSU, which is a public company that is partially state-funded.
